33300:Pair Production
33400:Pair Production
33500:pair production
33600:A phenomenon where both particles and antiparticles are generated upon the collision of a large amount of energy with a nucleus or something similar. In Dirac's Hole Theory, this is when the “vacuum collapses.”[linebreak][linebreak]Conversely, the collision of a particle and an antiparticle results in the annihilation of both particles.
33700:Nombre
