57800:Precognition
57900:Precognition
58000:precognition
58100:/ Pree-cog-nih-shin / (Noun) To know what is going to happen in advance, e.g. “To foresee an unusual phenomenon.” Also known as “foresight” or “foreknowledge.”[linebreak][linebreak]To know what is going to happen in the future before it actually happens. The term does not refer to predictions based on experience, information, or statistics, but rather a special sense that transcends humanity's natural perception. It has not been scientifically proven to exist.[linebreak][linebreak]The way it manifests differs from person to person, with the most common being visions and prophetic dreams.[linebreak][linebreak]Belief in precognition has existed since ancient times, where shrine maidens were often heralded as carriers. Psychics and fortune tellers are the modern incarnation of this belief, but there are many false actors who enjoy taking advantage of the superstition, claiming that they have precognitive powers in order to swindle others.
58200:Nombre
58300:Normie
58400:Normie
58500:normie
58600:People who find happiness and fulfillment in the real world.[linebreak][linebreak]Markers of a normie include having lots of friends, having a girlfriend or boyfriend, participating in club and/or school activities, going to parties, etc.
58700:Nombre
58800:Libido
58900:Libido
59000:libido
59100:According to Sigmund Freud, libido is “the energy that causes sexual impulses.” Carl Jung, meanwhile, defines it as “the body of energy that drives all instincts.”
