65600:An ideograph depicting a person on all fours, depressed. “o” is the head, “r” is the arms and torso, and “z” is the legs.[linebreak][linebreak]Typically used to express despair, dejection, or frustration.[linebreak][linebreak]There's no set way to pronounce it, and as such, people may pronounce it as “ortz,” “oars,” or “orse.”
